<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-39E500F9-28C4-4306-AF2D-2563082345A2" version="1" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-39E500F9-28C4-4306-AF2D-2563082345A2" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">06 Vacuum the chiller and check the fluid level (V2)</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="GUID-D809216A-81AD-49A6-991F-B4DB86389740"><p class="- topic/p ">It is advised to vacuum the chiller every month to keep the printer in the best condition. Vacuuming the chiller is part of periodic maintenance so the operator panel gives a warning when you should vacuum the chiller. Always check the fluid level when you vacuum the chiller. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Video: <ph class="- topic/ph " varid="Video: 7 - Vacuum the chiller"><xref class="- topic/xref " format="html" href="https://sus.cpp.canon/6V2H363P" scope="external"><?ditaot usertext?> 
<image class="- topic/image " href="GUID-1B93C780-C233-4810-947C-7EC17F913975-low.png" placement="inline" otherprops="GUID-1B93C780-C233-4810-947C-7EC17F913975-low.png"/> Vacuum the chiller</xref></ph> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The condenser surface is located directly behind the cover. This procedure describes the new design. 
</p><fig class="- topic/fig " id="GUID-AD69FFAC-1769-4152-BC0D-E02EEAB73969"><title class="- topic/title "/><image class="- topic/image " href="GUID-006253D2-E356-4A6F-82A7-4489BC71CE2A-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" otherprops="GUID-006253D2-E356-4A6F-82A7-4489BC71CE2A-low.png"/></fig></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">User task</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><prereq id="GUID-8DD2F718-077F-4873-AD92-3AD8C2590B7E" class="- topic/section task/prereq "><p class="- topic/p ">Use <ph varid="productname" class="- topic/ph ">Colorado M-Series</ph> prescribed: 
</p><ul id="UL_1A8B9254C67F4BE7A695F93E693619E8" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_4184E64F20A0410F88173C8B3481B064" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Screwdriver (Torx-25) 
</p></li><li id="LI_5D9B184942814EA9A8C10040ED9A6F74" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Vacuum cleaner with a brush head 
</p></li></ul></prereq><section id="GUID-30BEF56D-F52F-4278-80FB-A11650644FB6" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Check the fluid level</title><p class="- topic/p ">To check the fluid level, locate the level gauge glass behind the right-hand side of the cover. 
</p><note id="d25032e46" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">Do not remove this section of the cover. You can see the level gauge glass through the openings in the cover. 
</p></note><p class="- topic/p ">If the fluid level is near the bottom of the green zone, you must refill the chiller. 
</p><fig id="d25032e51" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-115D0E29-E59E-4C6B-828A-9214E9A62C6A-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-115D0E29-E59E-4C6B-828A-9214E9A62C6A-low.png"/></fig></section><steps id="GUID-7F838C04-3FFE-4D1A-A3A4-23C6A40D79AE" class="- topic/ol task/steps "><step id="d25032e54" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Go to the chiller side and locate the cover under the fan. 
</cmd></step><step id="d25032e57" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Unscrew the left and right screws on top of the cover with the Torx-25. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><fig id="d25032e61" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-F847F8F9-3D53-40B4-AA6B-233907EBBA3D-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-F847F8F9-3D53-40B4-AA6B-233907EBBA3D-low.png"/></fig></info></step><step id="d25032e63" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Lift the cover a little up and towards you (1), then lift it up fully and take it out (2). 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><fig id="d25032e67" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-DA662190-0F5C-4654-83ED-93B391692D8B-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-DA662190-0F5C-4654-83ED-93B391692D8B-low.png"/></fig></info></step><step id="d25032e69" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Vacuum the condenser surface as indicated. Make sure you remove all the collected dust. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><p class="- topic/p ">Do not remove any parts of the chiller. 
</p></info><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><note id="GUID-FEA87F98-9629-4E68-BE93-865AE4C54840" class="- topic/note " type="caution"><p class="- topic/p ">Vacuum the surface with care, make sure you do not damage the condenser surface. 
</p></note><fig id="d25032e78" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-5F465B74-2EEA-4B7C-BD03-4F71FDFC559D-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-5F465B74-2EEA-4B7C-BD03-4F71FDFC559D-low.png"/></fig></info></step><step id="d25032e80" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Place the cover back into position. 
</cmd></step><step id="d25032e83" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Fasten the left and right screws on top of the cover. 
</cmd></step><step id="d25032e86" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">When you vacuumed the chiller as part of periodic maintenance, on the operator panel tap on <ph class="- topic/ph "><uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "><text class="- topic/text ">Completed</text></uicontrol></ph> to end the maintenance action. 
</cmd></step></steps></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-96D013F9-74AE-4555-B4E4-FDA433643370.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>User task</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
</task>